<h1>LSST Brochure</h1>
<h5>The Widest, Fastest, Deepest, Eye of the New Digital Age</h5>
<p>The Large Synoptic Survey Telescope is a proposed wide-field
telescope facility with a qualitatively new capability to
open a fresh perspective on the universe.<p/> 
<h6>THE WORLD'S LARGEST DIGITAL CAMERA</h6>
<p>In order to take full advantage of its ten square-degree field of view,
the LSST will use a three billion pixel camera with a circular array of
189 innovative detector modules that stretches across 63 centimeters.
A novel monolithic 8.4-meter primary mirror and 5.2-meter tertiary
mirror combination will be kept in tight alignment with its 3.4-meter
wide secondary mirror.<br /><br />
The overall system will obtain sequential images of the entire observable sky, which can then be combined to provide a digital image of unprecedented depth and area coverage, or subtracted from each other to highlight celestial sources that change in brightness, position, or both. A distinguishing feature of the LSST approach is that science from the nearby solar system to "big picture" cosmology can be carried out in parallel, using a common set of images and the same  observation cadence to address a wide diversity of science goals.<p/><br />
